Pre-Game Insights: Namibia has requested that the match against Zimbabwe be played behind closed doors at the Orlando Stadium in Johannesburg due to financial challenges.
The Zimbabwe Football Association (ZIFA) spokesperson Mike Madoda confirmed that no fans will be allowed for either team.
This decision could be a strategic ploy by Namibia to hinder the Warriors from receiving overwhelming support from millions of Zimbabweans residing in South Africa.
A similar tactic was employed by Bafana Bafana in June when they hosted their World Cup qualifier against Zimbabwe in Bloemfontein.
